# S07-T08: Stress Tests

## Objective
Validate the system under telemetry burst conditions (100Hz frames, 1000+ targets).

## Acceptance Criteria
- `e2e/stress.spec.ts` injects 100Hz binary frame stream for 60s.
- Ring buffers do not overflow (no `undefined` reads).
- Decode error rate < 0.1%.
- HUD remains responsive (FPS ≥ 24 minimum under stress).
- `PERFORMANCE MODE ACTIVE` banner triggers when expected.

## Steps
1. Build frame generator producing synthetic high-rate binary payloads.
2. Mount full HUD; run for stress duration.
3. Sample FPS, decode error counter, ring overflow flags.
4. Assert thresholds; print diagnostics on failure.

## Invariants
- Stress duration ≥ 60s real-time.
- No assertions of exact frame counts (timing-sensitive); use rates/ratios.
- Failure must dump last 100 frames to artifact.
